Owing to increased life expectancy, patients with grown-up congenital heart 
disease nowadays present various types of arrhythmias. We report treatment of a 
27-year-old patient with tricuspid and pulmonary atresia who was referred to our 
department with symptomatic tachycardia. During electrophysiologic study, a 
