[The HIV population is aging].

[Article in Danish]

Hansen AB(1).

Author information:
(1)Lunge- og Infektionsmedicinsk Afdeling, Nordsjællands Hospital - Hillerød, 
Dyrehavevej 29, 3400 Hillerød. ann-brit.eg.hansen@regionh.dk.

The HIV population is aging due to increased life expectancy among HIV patients 
on antiretroviral therapy. 37% of Danish HIV patients are now older than 50 
years. Older age has implications for all stages of HIV care. Older patients are 
at higher risk of delayed HIV diagnosis and thereby less favourable prognosis. 
Factors related directly to HIV infection, lifestyle-related factors and 
co-infections contribute to increased prevalence of co-morbidity in older HIV 
patients, and medical treatments of co-morbidity together with three or more 
antiviral drugs increase the risk of polypharmacy.

